msgctxt "mn25:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 25 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 25 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn25:0.2"
msgid "Nivāpasutta "
msgstr "Fodder "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn25:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn25:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn25:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn25:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn25:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn25:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/some-translation-issues-in-the-nivapa-sutta/3897
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2, sc2
msgctxt "mn25:2.1"
msgid "“Na, bhikkhave, nevāpiko nivāpaṃ nivapati migajātānaṃ: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a trapper doesn’t cast bait for deer thinking, "

msgctxt "mn25:2.2"
msgid "‘imaṃ me nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ migajātā paribhuñjantā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ yāpentū’ti. "
msgstr "‘May the deer, enjoying this bait, be healthy and in good condition. May they live long and prosper!’ "

msgctxt "mn25:2.3"
msgid "Evañca kho, bhikkhave, nevāpiko nivāpaṃ nivapati migajātānaṃ: "
msgstr "A trapper casts bait for deer thinking, "

msgctxt "mn25:2.4"
msgid "‘imaṃ me nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ migajātā anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissanti, anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjissanti, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjissanti, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissanti imasmiṃ nivāpe’ti. "
msgstr "‘When these deer intrude on where I cast the bait, they’ll recklessly enjoy eating it. They’ll become indulgent, then they’ll become negligent, and then they’ll be vulnerable on account of this bait.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc3
msgctxt "mn25:3.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, paṭhamā migajātā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu, te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe. "
msgstr "And indeed, the first herd of deer intruded on where the trapper cast the bait and recklessly enjoyed eating it. They became indulgent, then they became negligent, and then they were vulnerable to the trapper on account of that bait. "

msgctxt "mn25:3.2"
msgid "Evañhi te, bhikkhave, paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā. "
msgstr "And that’s how the first herd of deer failed to get free from the trapper’s power. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli1.152, sc4
msgctxt "mn25:4.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, dutiyā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ: "
msgstr "So then a second herd of deer thought up a plan, "

msgctxt "mn25:4.2"
msgid "‘ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu. "
msgstr "‘The first herd of deer became indulgent … "

msgctxt "mn25:4.3"
msgid "Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn25:4.4"
msgid "Evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā. "
msgstr "and failed to get free of the trapper’s power. "

msgctxt "mn25:4.5"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we avoid eating the bait altogether? Avoiding dangerous food, we can venture deep into a wilderness region and live there.’ "

msgctxt "mn25:4.6"
msgid "Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭiviramiṃsu, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihariṃsu. "
msgstr "And that’s just what they did. "

msgctxt "mn25:4.7"
msgid "Tesaṃ gimhānaṃ pacchime māse, tiṇodakasaṅkhaye, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti. "
msgstr "But when it came to the last month of summer, the grass and water ran out. Their bodies became much too thin, "

msgctxt "mn25:4.8"
msgid "Tesaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyānaṃ balavīriyaṃ parihāyi. "
msgstr "and they lost their strength and energy. "

msgctxt "mn25:4.9"
msgid "Balavīriye parihīne tameva nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa paccāgamiṃsu. "
msgstr "So they went back to that same place where the trapper had cast bait. "

msgctxt "mn25:4.10"
msgid "Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu. "
msgstr "Intruding on that place, they recklessly enjoyed eating it … "

msgctxt "mn25:4.11"
msgid "Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn25:4.12"
msgid "Evañhi te, bhikkhave, dutiyāpi migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā. "
msgstr "And that’s how the second herd failed to get free from the trapper’s power. "

