msgstr "So the trapper and his companions thought, "

msgctxt "mn25:6.38"
msgid "‘sace kho mayaṃ catutthe migajāte ghaṭṭessāma, te ghaṭṭitā aññe ghaṭṭissanti te ghaṭṭitā aññe ghaṭṭissanti. "
msgstr "‘If we disturb this fourth herd of deer, they’ll disturb others, who in turn will disturb even more. "

msgctxt "mn25:6.39"
msgid "Evaṃ imaṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ sabbaso migajātā parimuñcissanti. "
msgstr "Then all of the deer will be free from this bait we’ve cast. "

msgctxt "mn25:6.40"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ catutthe migajāte ajjhupekkheyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we just keep an eye on that fourth herd?’ "

msgctxt "mn25:6.41"
msgid "Ajjhupekkhiṃsu kho, bhikkhave, nevāpiko ca nevāpikaparisā ca catutthe migajāte. "
msgstr "And that’s just what they did. "

msgctxt "mn25:6.42"
msgid "Evañhi te, bhikkhave, catutthā migajātā parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā. "
msgstr "And that’s how the fourth herd of deer got free from the trapper’s power. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc9
msgctxt "mn25:7.1"
msgid "Upamā kho me ayaṃ, bhikkhave, katā atthassa viññāpanāya. "
msgstr "I’ve made up this simile to make a point. "

msgctxt "mn25:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ cevettha attho—"
msgstr "And this is what it means. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn25:7.3"
msgid "nivāpoti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Bait’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn25:7.4"
msgid "Nevāpikoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ pāpimato adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Trapper’ is a term for Māra the Wicked. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn25:7.5"
msgid "Nevāpikaparisāti kho, bhikkhave, māraparisāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Trapper’s companions’ is a term for Māra’s assembly. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn25:7.6"
msgid "Migajātāti kho, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Deer’ is a term for ascetics and brahmins. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli1.156, sc10
msgctxt "mn25:8.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu. "
msgstr "Now, the first group of ascetics and brahmins intruded on where the bait and the material delights of the world were cast by Māra and recklessly enjoyed eating it. "

msgctxt "mn25:8.2"
msgid "Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise. "
msgstr "They became indulgent, then they became negligent, and then they were vulnerable to Māra on account of that bait and the material delights of the world. "

msgctxt "mn25:8.3"
msgid "Evañhi te, bhikkhave, paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā. "
msgstr "And that’s how the first group of ascetics and brahmins failed to get free from Māra’s power. "

msgctxt "mn25:8.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, paṭhamā migajātā tathūpame ahaṃ ime paṭhame samaṇabrāhmaṇe vadāmi. "
msgstr "This first group of ascetics and brahmins is just like the first herd of deer, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc11
msgctxt "mn25:9.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, dutiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ: "
msgstr "So then a second group of ascetics and brahmins thought up a plan, "

msgctxt "mn25:9.2"
msgid "‘ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu. "
msgstr "‘The first group of ascetics and brahmins became indulgent … "

msgctxt "mn25:9.3"
msgid "Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn25:9.4"
msgid "Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā. "
msgstr "and failed to get free of Māra’s power. "

msgctxt "mn25:9.5"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we avoid eating the bait and the world’s material delights altogether? Avoiding dangerous food, we can venture deep into a wilderness region and live there.’ "

# NOTE: This a ghost sentence, formed by adding the first part of the subsequent sentence with the second part of the previous. It is absent from the PTS text.
msgctxt "mn25:9.6"
msgid "Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭiviramiṃsu, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn25:9.7"
msgid "Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭiviramiṃsu, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihariṃsu. "
msgstr "And that’s just what they did. "

msgctxt "mn25:9.8"
msgid "Te tattha sākabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, sāmākabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, nīvārabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, daddulabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, haṭabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, kaṇabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, ācāmabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, piññākabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, tiṇabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, gomayabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, vanamūlaphalāhārā yāpesuṃ pavattaphalabhojī. "
msgstr "They ate herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survived on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.157, sc12
msgctxt "mn25:9.9"
msgid "Tesaṃ gimhānaṃ pacchime māse, tiṇodakasaṅkhaye, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti. "
msgstr "But when it came to the last month of summer, the grass and water ran out. Their bodies became much too thin, "

msgctxt "mn25:9.10"
msgid "Tesaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyānaṃ balavīriyaṃ parihāyi. "
msgstr "and they lost their strength and energy. "

msgctxt "mn25:9.11"
msgid "Balavīriye parihīne cetovimutti parihāyi. "
msgstr "Because of this, they lost their heart’s release, "

msgctxt "mn25:9.12"
msgid "Cetovimuttiyā parihīnāya tameva nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa paccāgamiṃsu tāni ca lokāmisāni. "
msgstr "so they went back to that same place where Māra had cast the bait and the material delights of the world. "

msgctxt "mn25:9.13"
msgid "Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu. "
msgstr "Intruding on that place, they recklessly enjoyed eating them … "

msgctxt "mn25:9.14"
msgid "Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn25:9.15"
msgid "Evañhi te, bhikkhave, dutiyāpi samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā. "
msgstr "And that’s how the second group of ascetics and brahmins failed to get free from Māra’s power. "

